  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh: Addressing Trafficking and Smuggling through Improved Border Management and Counter Trafficking Responses in Cox&apos;s Bazar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM will work to increase awareness among Rohingya about existing mechanisms for reporting trafficking in persons and lodging grievances with agencies. IOM will also work with the government to strengthen intra- and inter-agency communication and coordination, as well as to improve their technical capacities to effectively manage the border, curb irregular movements, and respond to counter- trafficking and counter-migrants smuggling challenges. Urgent protection initiatives targeting victims or potential victims of trafficking, in particular women heads of households and unaccompanied migrant children, and the emergency capacitation of law enforcement and border management duty bearers will be prioritized. The interventions will increase awareness and usage of border management and counter-trafficking mechanisms, whilst simultaneously building coordination between border management entities, strengthening their capacity and promoting the wellbeing and rights of migrants.</narrative>
  </description>
